# Brahmi OCR — Implementation Walkthrough

## What Was Built

Complete pipeline from synthetic data to inference for Brahmi script OCR using TrOCR.

### Files Changed

| File | Action | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| [generate_synthetic.py](file:///c:/Users/tejas/OneDrive/Desktop/brahmi_ocr_project/dataset/generate_synthetic.py) | NEW | Synthetic dataset generator (chars, words, phrases with augmentations) |
| [preprocess.py](file:///c:/Users/tejas/OneDrive/Desktop/brahmi_ocr_project/utils/preprocess.py) | REWRITE | OpenCV preprocessing: denoise, threshold, CLAHE, resize |
| [dataset_loader.py](file:///c:/Users/tejas/OneDrive/Desktop/brahmi_ocr_project/training/dataset_loader.py) | REWRITE | PyTorch Dataset with TrOCRProcessor integration |
| [train.py](file:///c:/Users/tejas/OneDrive/Desktop/brahmi_ocr_project/training/train.py) | REWRITE | TrOCR fine-tuning with FP16, AdamW, best-model saving |
| [predict.py](file:///c:/Users/tejas/OneDrive/Desktop/brahmi_ocr_project/inference/predict.py) | REWRITE | Model loading + inference CLI |
| [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/tejas/OneDrive/Desktop/brahmi_ocr_project/requirements.txt) | UPDATE | Added sentencepiece, numpy, tqdm, matplotlib |
| [README.md](file:///c:/Users/tejas/OneDrive/Desktop/brahmi_ocr_project/README.md) | UPDATE | Full usage docs with CLI options tables |

## Verification

### Synthetic dataset test run

Generated 25 images with `--num_chars 10 --num_words 10 --num_phrases 5`:

- ✅ **25 PNG images** created in `dataset/images/`
- ✅ **labels.txt** has 25 tab-separated entries with Brahmi Unicode text
- ✅ **Splits**: train (20) / val (2) / test (3) — matches 80/10/10 ratio
- ✅ **Visual quality**: Brahmi characters rendered on textured backgrounds with rotation

